Anonymous Sun 23 Dec 2018 15:15:25 No.20195854 Report

>>20195031
> why does everyone use pastebin?

It's quick and it's more discrete. It's like a sketchpad for writing. You can even post things without creating an account (but then you lose the ability to edit it in the future).

If you post your stuff on an actual gallery like FA or SoFurry, then people will immediately take what you write to a higher standard. So for things that were jotted down in a half hour, Pastebin feels more appropriate. I agree it's a bit odd, but it's become standard image-board etiquette.

Hi Anon! Glad to see someone else looking to get into the writing game. Happy, as well to see that you're interested in trying something new from the usual fare here.

With that being the case, I would warn that unless you try for a radically different waifur (I.E. something cold-blooded, venomous, invertebrate, etc.) the story isn't going to run /ALL/ that differently. At the end of the day, what really makes a story unique are the circumstances, the world, and the perspective.

If you want to really break from the mold, here, you might consider trying to write a FAOHM
story instead of the typical HMOFA fare. writing a story from the waifur's perspective will give you a chance to really play up the anthro characteristics from her perspective. You can go over differences in sight, sound, and smell, and can talk about her mental processes (especially when animalistic tendencies tend to play up)

Just a thought.
